## Limit Justification

`CANCELLATION_GRADE_THRESHOLD = 0.70`: calibrated on the 16 GR photon-sphere cases. The three catastrophic naive cases emit grades `0.985172682307`, `0.989068229867`, and `0.971615210307`, all above the limit. The expected-clean naive cases remain below the limit: `F1_along_B` `0.558520201728`, `F2_along_r` `0.335704810951`, `F2_along_B` `0.594664325259`; stable nonzero power-law cases remain clean.

`DROP_RATE_THRESHOLD = 0.30`: calibrated so the expected-clean GR drop cases remain accepted (`naive_F1_along_B` `0.125`, `naive_F2_along_B` `0.25`) while synthetic mixed finite/nonfinite evidence at `0.333333333333` emits `sweep_signature_high_drop_rate`. `naive_F2_along_tangent` has drop rate `0.375`, but cancellation precedence classifies it as cancellation-dominated first.

`MIN_OBSERVATIONS_FOR_FIT = 3`: inherited from the composed `typed_log_log_slope` ordinary-least-squares minimum; synthetic two-cell evidence emits `sweep_signature_insufficient_data`.

